708024f-a.title: Manhattan: 3rd Avenue - 22nd Street (East)
708024f-a.text:
Third Ave., east side, no th from, but not including East 22nd Street,
showing (promtnently), a portion of the building until recently occupied by
the New York Opthalmic Hospital; also known as the Henry Keep Pavilion; erect-
ed in 1871 by Emna A. Keep.  This hospital is now (1937), located at No. 1
East 105th Street, in the building of the Fifth Ave. Hospital, at the N.E.
corner of East 105th Street. Also shown is the 23rd Street station of the
Third Ave. Elevated Line.
December 23, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
